From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Alice C. Munduruca" <alice.munduruca@canonical.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 09:48:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] UBUNTU: SAUCE: Fix jump__delete for perftools.

BugLink: https://bugs.launchpad.net/bugs/2157654

A mistake was introduced when adjusting the context for commit c760ca126deb7
("perf annotate: use jump__delete when freeing LoongArch jumps"). This
was not caught by CBD as it doesn't build tools by default.

Signed-off-by: Alice C. Munduruca <alice.munduruca@canonical.com>
---
 tools/perf/util/annotate.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/tools/perf/util/annotate.c b/tools/perf/util/annotate.c
index 69348078b6c028dbe3a166b30732e57d8c3bbbe3..0117004b47d48f68e565bc516987770521e56bd8 100644
--- a/tools/perf/util/annotate.c
+++ b/tools/perf/util/annotate.c
@@ -71,7 +71,7 @@ static int call__scnprintf(struct ins *ins, char *bf, size_t size,
 			  struct ins_operands *ops, int max_ins_name);
 static int jump__scnprintf(struct ins *ins, char *bf, size_t size,
 			  struct ins_operands *ops, int max_ins_name);
-static int jump__delete(struct ins_operands *ops);
+static void jump__delete(struct ins_operands *ops);
 
 struct arch {
 	const char	*name;
